23/05/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Authorities on Monday (22 May) put some 13,000 people in quarantine and closed all businesses in a district in Bucharest for a period of up to three weeks because of an outbreak of bird flu.
Some 40 streets have been sealed off in the capital's Luica quarter.
Teams of veterinary experts have started to cull several thousand domestic birds in the area.
Agriculture Minister Gheorghe Flutur says there are currently 34 confirmed cases of bird flu in the country, including those in Bucharest and the counties of Brasov, Sibiu, Valcea, Vrancea and Neamt.
(Nine o'clock - 23/05/06;
AFP - 22/05/06)
